## Standard Schema over library-specific APIs

Prefer **@standard-schema/spec** types and the standard interfaces so code works with any spec-compliant library (Zod, Valibot, ArkType, etc.) instead of coupling to one.

### Types to use

- **StandardSchemaV1** ‚Äì For validation/parsing. Has `~standard.validate(value)` (sync or async). Use this in option types, plugin options, and route schema parameters when you accept ‚Äúa schema‚Äù from the user.
- **StandardJSONSchemaV1** ‚Äì For JSON Schema conversion when needed. Has `~standard.jsonSchema.input(options)` / `.output(options)` with `target: 'draft-2020-12' | 'draft-07' | 'openapi-3.0'`. Use when generating OpenAPI, MCP tool schemas, or other JSON Schema output.

Import only from `@standard-schema/spec` for these types (e.g. `import type { StandardSchemaV1 } from "@standard-schema/spec"`). Do not depend on `zod`, `valibot`, or `arktype` in shared/core code.

### In public APIs and options

- **Schema options**: Type as `StandardSchemaV1` (or `StandardJSONSchemaV1` if you only need JSON Schema conversion). Example: `schema?: StandardSchemaV1` on direct/mcp options.
- **Validation**: Call `schema['~standard'].validate(value)` (and handle `result.issues` / `result.value`). Do not use `z.parse()`, `v.parse()`, or library-specific APIs in framework or package code that should accept any compliant schema.
- **JSON Schema from a schema**: If the schema has `~standard.jsonSchema?.input`, call `schema['~standard'].jsonSchema.input({ target: 'draft-2020-12' })` (or the draft you need). Do not use `z.toJSONSchema()` or library-specific converters in shared code.
- **Type inference from schema**: When an adapter accepts a Standard Schema (e.g. `direct()`/`mcp()` `schema`, `llm()` `outputSchema`), use `StandardSchemaV1.InferOutput<S>` so the body or result type is inferred when the option is provided; when omitted, keep the type as `unknown` (or the adapter default). This gives typed routes without manual generics.

### In examples and docs

- Examples can use any compliant library (Zod, Valibot, ArkType). Prefer showing one (e.g. Zod) for clarity, but mention that any Standard Schema implementation works.
- When documenting ‚Äúschema‚Äù parameters or options, refer to ‚ÄúStandard Schema‚Äù or ‚ÄúStandardSchemaV1‚Äù and link to [standardschema.dev](https://standardschema.dev) or the repo‚Äôs rule; avoid ‚Äúmust use Zod‚Äù unless it‚Äôs an example-only note.

### When library-specific code is acceptable

- **Tests** may use a single library (e.g. Zod) for convenience.
- **Example apps** may use one library for the whole example.
- **Validation of plugin/config options** can use a specific library if that validation is internal and not exposed as ‚Äúaccept any schema.‚Äù

### References

- Standard Schema: [standardschema.dev](https://standardschema.dev)
- Standard JSON Schema: [standardschema.dev/json-schema](https://standardschema.dev/json-schema)
- Package: `@standard-schema/spec` (already a dependency in routecraft and ai)
